description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Superintendent Radiographer for Community based X-Ray Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our staff have gained an excellent reputation for providing a high quality x-ray service. We are looking for a highly motivated Superintendent Radiographer to lead our community x-ray departments to provide an outstanding imaging service to our local community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The x-ray departments undertake approximately 25,000 examinations per year. We have x-ray sites in Walton on Thames and Woking. We work with state of the art equipment - having 2 Siemens YSIOS DR suites. We work closely with the Walk in Centre’s, Outpatients Department, Inpatients and GP’s. You will have to be self-motivated and able to work on your own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic band 7 radiographer who will work clinically as well as undertake managerial duties. The successful candidate will have experience of leading a team and managing workflows. You will need to be dynamic and flexible approach and be prepared to participate in the rotas which include evening and weekend duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will have either a DCR or a BSc qualification and have extensive knowledge and experience of radiographic procedures. A high standard of radiographic technique is essential with a patient centered approach to your work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look for people who are willing to go the extra mile, not because they are asked to, but because they are committed to being part of a healthcare team that delivers an excellent and caring service to our patients. If you want to part of a friendly department with a patient centered focus, then please apply.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you are interested in meeting the staff and seeing the departments, please contact Carol Marsden (carolmarsden@nhs.net) or the Woking x-ray department on 01483 846315&lt;/p&gt;
